				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\beta $\end{document}β. The occurrence is weakly dependent on the solar wind density and dynamic pressure, with lower values appearing to be more favourable for jet formation. There is no absolute consensus whether an increase in IMF magnitude (relative to the base solar wind distribution for each study) is favourable for jet formation of jets or not, although the absolute values for jet detection agree in the studies. Table 1
