Using multispacecraft observations from the THEMIS mission, Pöppelwerth et al. (2024a) developed a method for estimating the sizes of jets perpendicular to the direction of propagation and applied the method to a single jet. They found that the perpendicular size increased from the leading part of the jet toward the center and decreased from the center toward the trailing part, with the maximum size being \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
